## 📄 Core Features

### 1. Load PDF (Local Only)

* Use `<input type="file" accept="application/pdf">`
* Read file as ArrayBuffer
* Load with pdf-lib
### 2. Render PDF Pages

* Use canvas to render pages (via PDF.js OR custom renderer)
* Each page displayed vertically
* Support zoom in/out
### 3. Annotation Layer (IMPORTANT)

Implement overlay system:

Each page has:

* base canvas (PDF render)
* overlay canvas (annotations)

Support:

* Add text box
* Highlight (semi-transparent rectangle)
* Free draw (mouse)
* Insert image

Store annotations in state:

```ts
type Annotation = {
  id: string
  page: number
  type: "text" | "highlight" | "draw" | "image"
  x: number
  y: number
  width?: number
  height?: number
  content?: string
  color?: string
}
```
### 4. Toolbar (Top)

Actions:

* Add Text
* Highlight
* Draw
* Insert Image
* Delete selected
* Undo / Redo
### 5. Thumbnail Strip (Bottom)

* Horizontal scroll
* Show all pages
* Click → scroll to page
* Highlight current page
### 6. Page Operations

Using pdf-lib:

* Delete page
* Reorder pages (drag & drop)
* Duplicate page
* Merge another PDF
### 7. Export PDF

On export:

* Re-open original PDF
* Apply annotations:

  * draw text using `drawText`
  * draw rectangles for highlights
  * embed images
* Generate new PDF
* Download file
### 8. State Management

Use React state or Zustand-style store:

* currentPage
* zoomLevel
* annotations[]
* selectedTool
### 9. UI/UX

* TailwindCSS clean UI
* Dark mode support
* Floating toolbar
* Smooth scroll
* Cursor changes based on tool
* Resize & drag annotations
## ⚡ Performance

* Lazy render pages (only visible ones)
* Debounce scroll
* Avoid re-render full document
* Use requestAnimationFrame for drawing
## 🧪 Edge Cases

* Large PDFs (100+ pages)
* Fast scrolling
* Undo/redo stack
* Memory cleanup
## 🚫 Constraints

* No backend
* No upload to server
* No OCR
* No real text editing inside PDF stream
## ✅ Expected Result

User can:

* Open PDF locally
* View pages smoothly
* Add annotations visually
* Navigate via thumbnails
* Export edited PDF
